[1] Cases in various countries
Americas
---
North America
---
USA:
- Florida, California. 19 Mar 2019. (conf.) as of 18 Mar 2019, the states of California and Florida confirmed 14 Zika cases during 2019, all imported from countries where Zika virus is circulating.
http://www.promedmail.org/dashboard/index.php?m=2

- Cases in children. 19 Mar 2019. (reported) Researchers assessed data from children who met the case definition for confirmed or probable ZIKV infection with symptom onset beginning between 2016 and 2017. All children (n = 141) were aged younger than 18 years and resided in California, Indiana, Maryland, Massachusetts, Minnesota, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Texas or Virginia.
Most children infected were aged 12 to 17 years (64%), followed by children aged 5 to 11 years (30%) and children aged 1 to 4 years (5%). One child was aged younger than 1 year. Nearly all children (99%) were infected with ZIKV while traveling to a country or territory outside the U.S. Lindsey and colleagues said Mexico (n = 28), the Dominican Republic (n = 26) and Puerto Rico (n = 22) were the most commonly travel destinations. There were 2 children infected in Texas by mosquito transmission, they said. According to the researchers, 89% (n = 125) of children had lab-confirmed ZIKV infection.

The researchers observed no neurologic signs or symptoms of ZIKV infection in children. The most commonly reported clinical signs and symptoms were rash (94%), fever (74%), arthralgia (48%) and conjunctivitis (51%). The rashes were most often maculopapular, and about half were pruritic. Most children (87%) had 2 or more signs or symptoms, with 70% reporting fever and rash. More than half of the children had 3 or more signs and symptoms, and 18% had 4.
https://www.healio.com/pediatrics/emerging-diseases/news/online/%7B75cd8cfa-474d-4e1b-8877-787fce81252b%7D/postnatal-zika-infection-symptoms-mirror-common-childhood-illnesses

