Asia
---
Taiwan ex Viet Nam. 20 Feb 2019. (conf.) A junior high school boy developed a fever the day before he returned from a 10-day holiday with his family in Ho Chih Minh City, and his abnormal temperature was detected at a screening station on his arrival at Taichung International Airport on 15 Feb 2019, the Taiwan CDC said.
http://focustaiwan.tw/news/asoc/201902200030.aspx

[A 21 Feb 2019 report indicated that since 2016, there have been 21 cases of Zika virus infections in Taiwan, all of which have been imported, with countries in Southeast Asia being the major source, according to Taiwan CDC statistics. https://outlook.office.com/owa/?realm=wisc.edu&path=/mail/inbox/rp]

HealthMap/ProMED-mail maps:
Taiwan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6377153,193
Viet Nam: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6377153,152

Thailand. 27 Feb 2019. (published) The study assessed the long-term circulation of Zika virus in Thailand. The spatial and age distribution of cases were analyzed, and constructed time-resolved phylogenetic trees using genomes from Thailand and elsewhere to estimate when Zika virus was 1st introduced. Of the 3089 samples from 1717 symptomatic individuals tested between January 2016, and December 2017, 368 were confirmed to have Zika virus infection. Cases of Zika virus infection were reported throughout the year, and from 29 of the 76 Thai provinces. Phylogenetic reconstructions suggest persistent circulation within Thailand since at least 2002. Evidence shows that Zika virus has circulated at a low but sustained level for at least 16 years, suggesting that Zika virus can adapt to persistent endemic transmission.
https://www.thelancet.com/journals/laninf/article/PIIS1473-3099(18)30718-7/fulltext

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map:
Thailand: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6377153,151]

